<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/karana.cgi?read=64" TARGET=_self>Brother PAL. &gt;Ghoulbane</A> (Neilwood)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Hail Brother,
<P>Actually you are wrong, I traded for a Ghoulbane 5 days ago. Furthermore dont bother hunting for it in Gukk untill you have a full party of about lvl 30 players. You must also have lots of patience, the NPC is a VERY rare spawn and spawns with Ghoulbane even less. I have heard of groups camping for 2 weeks for the sword and only killing the NPC 10 times in that period, and NOT ever having recieved Ghoulbane as loot. Hope I have not discouraged you. But if you are ever blessed with being able to weild the mighty sword you will be most pleased. I have gone from doing max damage per hit with a PGT of 15 to 40 with Ghoulbane. Not to mention when fighting undead when it occasionally casts Dismiss Undead for about 144 points of damage. Good Luck in your quest for a Holy Sword young knight, they are few and hard to come by.
<P>Sir Garrid Draxx
<BR>Paladin of the 28th Order
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
